cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.MA 

The paper proposes a learning-based handover optimization for the Internet of Vehicles using machine learning algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of fog computing, which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of request routing, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
